<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I need some info on how tough this is to get and what is needed to do it.<P>I understand that you need to kill some mobs in the arena in Kael.<P>1) How tough are these mobs? Is this a single group event? I'm a 59 almost 60 cleric now and I can grab a bunch of 60s or near-60s to help if needed.<P>2) What are the factions on these mobs? I am on +Kael faction and I need to know how much if any of a hit I am looking at taking from this. Is this easier to do with a bunch of +Kael folks?<P>3) Which mobs precisely drop the idols and how rare are they?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Irysangel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I could use some advice on this too. I know the idol-holders are behind the arena (You will lose both Storm Giant and Frost Giant faction, btw, and possibly King faction).<P>I have the idols of corruption and disease both. I haven't seen hide nor hair of the other two in the umpteen Kael raids we've done. Someone said that one of the idols drops off of Kallis. Is this true? We kill him every time we go and he never drops anything but that smushed head for a ranger quest.<P>Just curious. Anyone else had any luck with this?  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lladra</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gkrean Prophet of Tallon and Semkak Prophet of Vallon, I got idols off of. And I got an idol off a cleric of vallon zek also. Need idol of errosion now and I am done.  FYI these idols weigh a ton, 6.5wt each.<P>Good luck.<P>Lladra of Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Omniscience</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gkrean Prophet of Tallon and Semkak Prophet of Vallon drop the same idols everytime. And other 2 idols are random and rare off any clerics or priests with them.<BR>One very good group may able to do it. You need a puller that knows how to split 3 high lv giants, enc that can keep your mana good and tash, a shm for slowing, a very good tank, an evacer or a dmg dealer for safe or kill fast. Oh yeah, the enc has to drain giant cleric's mana too or they will gate away at end. 2 groups would be much safer tho.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rainessa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is there a lvl limit for this?  On Allakazams it just mentioned lvl 46, but some guildmates were telling me you have to be lvl 55 to actually do the quest.  I havent read anything yet that points either way on this, I was hoping to finish the quest and then be free to assist guild in PoG but lvl 55 seems far away :/<P>Rainessa Concordia 53 Bard<BR>Leesa Lluvia 51 Cleric<BR>Noble Blade of the Rathe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lladra</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">55 i have heard, I multied a fleshless skull for a paladin, grats Illanae on second Nature Defender, but waited to do it at 55, *shrug* the quest mob seeks Knights and Templars, ie 55paly and clerics.<P>Lladra of Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aerie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The person getting the quest reward need to be 55+. Otherwise the Guardian will eat your idols up.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Elessara</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hard thing about these guys isn't really the mobs themselves - although they are kinda tough.  Its the 3 protectors of zek that you have to pull before you get to the Prophets and clerics.  It is almost impossible to get these guys single.  I've had a couple of very good lvl 59/60 monks try it and what happens is they will pull a single and then another (or both) one will port on top of them.  The protectors hit for 360 and they hit VERY fast.  It IS possible for one group to kill them all but it involves kiting.  If you're in the actual arena, there's not much room (its doable, I've been in a group where we've done it).  If you're on the other side, where the adjudants, troopers, legionnaires and veterans spawn you MUST keep this area cleared.  I've been in single groups that have done it both ways.  In my case, we had a totally insane druid kiting both times.  The protectors are not mezzable (like all giants) and they are not charmable except by Dictate.<P>Two idols seem to always drop from the Prophets.  The other two idols should drop randomly from the clerics.  The idols do NOT drop from Kallis.<P>I'm not sure how easy it would be to do with people who are on +Kael faction.  I'm on Dragon faction myself.  You will take negative faction hits with Kromzek, Kromriff, King Tormax and you will get a positive faction hit with Claws of Veeshan.  Again I'm not sure how bad a hit you will get.<P>You don't have to have a shaman for slowing, the ench can do that just fine, although most ench I know don't like to slow, so having a shaman would be good.  The group I was with the first time (when we killed them in the arena) was myself, a druid, an ench, a shaman, a paladin and a necro.  I've also done it with a wizard, an sk, a necro, an ench and a monk.<P>Elessara DeathTouched<BR>High Priestess of Tunare<BR>Cats in Hats<BR>Drinal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eachann</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When you hail the quest giver, he says right off the bat that he is looking for a Knight or a Templar of Tunare.   That means that you have to be level 55  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>Eachann Bronzeleaf<BR>Templar of Tunare, <BR>Tarew Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lladra</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just completed this last night.<P>I got the idol of errosion off of a priest of vallon.<P>-Lladra</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I haven't quite been able to piece together who drops what, can someone help me out?<P>Corruption: Gkrean Prophet <BR>Disease:  Semkak Prophet of Vallon<BR>Decay:   Cleric of Tallon/Vallon Zek<BR>Erosion: Cleric of Tallon/Vallon Zek<P>Is this correct?<BR><p>[This message has been edited by electrae (edited 06-10-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lladra</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i got errosion off a priest</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gryfalia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Er, nothing against your monk pullers, but<BR>we spent a LOT of time behind the arena and<BR>we managed to pull every single critter<BR>there single, protectors of Zek or not.<P>Doesn't mean it didn't take forever, and<BR>occasionally kill the poor monk doing the<BR>deed, but except for one time where 2<BR>people both pulled one (yeah, that made<BR>sense) we always got singles..<P>Gryfalia<BR>52 Vicar of Brell<BR>Imperial Guards<BR>Druzzil Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Resurrector</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is the quest giver in POG on POG faction?<P>I'm wondering since I'm kos in pog.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P><BR>Resurrector<BR>Cleric of the 59th<BR>Defender of the Faith<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Escapee</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How rare are the other two idols? Like 1 in 4? 1 in 10? 1 in 50? Just want to set my expectations straight on how many giants it's going to take...<P>Escapee </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cayleu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yep, if you are a high elf cleric who has been cast out of the Tunarean faith by daring to desecrate the mother of all's land, then you may as well forget about ever seeing this wonderful bracer. If your kos to pog, then you are also kos to the quest-giver.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
